Name: Antigua Guatemala
Description: Antigua Guatemala - UNESCO World Heritage Site. A city founded in the early 16th century, showcasing Spanish colonial architecture with well-preserved Baroque buildings.

Name: Tikal National Park
Description: Tikal National Park - UNESCO World Heritage Site. An ancient Maya city with impressive temples and palaces, one of the largest archaeological sites of the pre-Columbian Maya civilization.

Name: Archaeological Park and Ruins of Quiriguá
Description: Archaeological Park and Ruins of Quiriguá - UNESCO World Heritage Site. A site containing outstanding carved stelae and sculpted calendars from the Maya civilization.
